name: Save The Princess
lore: Your princess is in another castle. Isn't she always? Princess Foxia has been kidnapped and it's up to you, intrepid heroes, to bring her home to Castle Vulpes. Armed with only your wits, whatever you could pick up at the local pawn shop, and some strange looking mushrooms that you're convinced don't have magical powers but might make the world look funny for a few hours; you'll battle the wilderness, the castle guards (at multiple castles), and The Boss.

name: The Sword From The Stone
lore: Does a crown alone make a King? Or is there more to it? Legends say that when the genesis block was formed, Hexcalibur -- or 0xcalibur as it's known in the Ether Lands -- was formed with it, inside of a rock formation. In the mythos, whoever can pull the sword from its resting place shall be recognized as the King of foxkind, though it's just as likely he'll just have a very cool-looking sword. Still, worth a try, right?

name: The Fables of Longbeard
lore: Somewhere among the highest peaks of the Foxton Range, the shack of Alton Longbeard can be found. Now, a recluse, but once, the greatest beardkeeper in Foxton's Chevron district. Little is known about why Longbeard took to the mountains, but the greatest bearded foxes seek to learn his secrets, to preserve the traditions of Foxton's barber shops. Can your band of foxes locate Longbeard and learn his secrets?

name: The Treasure of Shipwreck Cove
lore: Rumor has it that the ancient treasures of Captain Blacktail are buried somewhere near Shipwreck Cove, but do you have the seafaring skills to find it? Tales tell of an emerald imbued ring that confers the power to control the winds, but they're probably nothing -- either way, it's expensive. This mission isn't for the landlubbers, so what say ye?

name: Moonshot Dreams
lore: Deep in downtown Kitson lies the casino district: home to the deprived, degenerate, and the lucky. There are whispers of an underground ring for the best card players, where thousands of FOXY are won and lost in a single round of cards. Can you pull off a winning night at the illustrious table, or will you just be left huffing copium?

name: The Ihsotas Otomakan
lore: Foxes who wish to ascend to the highest ranks of the Hallowed Skulk are tasked with a process, starting at the Elyssian Plains, which will push their mind, body and spirit to the absolute limits. Only those who achieve the higher state at the Hyperuranion will achieve ascension into the Skulk's inner circle. Is your fox ready for the ultimate challenge?

name: The Lunar Landing
lore: This is it, the ultimate purpose of FASA: the conquest of the harshest realities of nature to reach the Moon. Space is an unnatural atmosphere for foxes, composed entirely of threats which could prevent the uninitiated from reaching the moon. Low oxygen, potential impacts with debris, bearish sentiment and the dreaded FUD monster won't stop FASA from reaching its target though, will it?

name: Like No One Ever Was
lore: Monster trainers do their thing all year around, but once a year, Fohxto hosts the Orange League Championship: an intercontinental tournament of the brightest and bravest foxes and their partners. Only the most elite will make their way to the Orange League finals in Foxter City. Will your fox be among them?

name: A Culinary Conundrum
lore: Fanged foxes aren't actually vampires, but that doesn't stop them from playing into a popular rumor for fame and fortune. The infamous blood red sauce of Foxylvania has run out, and no one remembers the recipe. It's up to your fanged friend to undergo a test of palate and procurement to recreate the sauce from taste alone.

name: Lost in the Wilderness
lore: The call has just come in at the Safari hut. Another fox has gone off-track looking for the perfect selfie for their influencer blog. Unfortunately, selfies with lions and tigers don't always end well for the one taking them. Armed only with his wits and experience, your fox is tasked with retrieving the guy who's about to become Famous for all the wrong reasons.

name: The First Rule of [Redacted]
lore: Foxes don't talk about it, that's against the rules, but under various pseudonyms and wearing prominent headbands, they definitely participate in it. Tyler Furden's legacy is up for grabs in an abandoned warehouse on the outskirts of Foxton. Are your foxes capable of conquering the challenge, and winning in the ultimate tournament of that-which-cannot-be-named?

name: Uncharted Shores
lore: Little is known about Aether Island, but after your Kitten procured a map from Sun's stash, your Fox and Kitten decided to explore it in search of bounty and plunder. Will they discover the secrets of the Chromatic Cascade, or swing from the vines of the Thriving Thicket? Will they find the source of the Island's power?

name: The Thug Life
lore: Nothing is more enticing to a member of the Thug Life gang than the chance to pull a hilarious prank on an unsuspecting Fox. Taking everything you’ve learned from the hit TV show Fox’d, you set out to pull off the ultimate prank for all of the bragging rights!

name: Prepare for Glory
lore: In Civitas Vulpes, much ado is made about history -- historical leaders, historical romances, but most of all, historical battles. Unfortunately, much of this is based on rumor and legend, as there are few verifiable recordings of that far back in time. One rumor has it that the land upon which Trastevere now sits played host to the Battle of the Bushels, and that the evidence may lay below the city itself in a secret network of tunnels that were used in wartime to deliver messages. Will your fox be able to locate the tunnels, and recover ancient artefacts which would restore Trastevere to glory?

name: School of Fox
lore: The Games are well known among the collegiate. A series of competitions between the four great institutions of academia which confer prizes, the right to host the next Games, but most of all, bragging rights. Can your fox show the smarts, the wits, and the gusto to lead the College to victory?

name: I'm not saying it was aliens...
lore: Mutant dens are not like other dens, and other foxes have noticed it for a long time. It's fuelled all kinds of rumors: are the mutants psychic? Do they come from a nuclear catastrophe? The reality, of course, is quite a bit harder to believe. The tribe themselves have long been known to keep their origins a secret, especially from those probing minds at FASA, and with new legislation pending which would allow FASA to investigate, there's not much time to hide the evidence. Can your fox lead the mutant tribe to protect the secrets of their origins?

name: The Captain Furfang Conundrum
lore: Captain Furfang's legacy is famous among the Captain's guild, and none of his adventures is more famous than his rivalry with Captain Jack Burrows. Now, the Guild has come upon a mysterious unsigned message, which claims to know the location of Furfang's remains, and his prized coat and hat. The problem is, they're at the bottom of the ocean. Can your foxes finally prove the existence of their Guild's legend, and return his prized possessions to the Guildhouse?

name: The Search for Satoshi
lore: With crypto dumping like a bad date, the alpha seekers have decided that the only way to save their favorite methods of investment and interaction is to find Satoshi, and get him to please do something. Will your foxes -- traditional rivals -- be able to put their differences aside and make the price go up, or will the mission just devolve into an endless discussion about usability versus security?

name: A Clothing Conundrum
lore: Due to rising instances of shoplifting, some of the stores in Foxton's upmarket district of Dali have started banning wearing hoodies and baseball caps in their shops. Hoodies have long been a fashion preference of a large number of foxes, and having to change their wardrobe just to be able to get some groceries or a pair of sneakers seems unreasonable to them. Can your fox lead a successful protest and get the store owners to change their minds?

name: Be Prepared!
lore: Scarred foxes have long been subject to legends among other foxes; sometimes, these legends lionize them as great warriors, but other times, they associate them with a character from a certain movie about lions. In order to retain their more positive perception, scarred foxes often take it upon themselves to do something exceptionally brave. So when a tornado comes to town, your fox takes it upon themself to lead the others to safety! Can they find a safe route out of town?

name: Im-Mead-iate Solution Required
lore: Hvergelmir can withstand most problems: sea monsters, blizzards, and avalanches. What it cannot withstand is a lack of alcohol, and that's exactly what's coming up. Due to a production shortage at the local brewery due to a weak harvest, someone is going to have to import mead from Asgard. There's only one problem: a typhoon out at sea. Can your fox navigate the treacherous waters and restore the town's most important resource?

name: Knitting a Tangle
lore: Spring is upon Foxton, and the demand for scarves is waning; however, there remains a huge demand for the knitted neckwear in the frozen northern town of Asgard. Can your fox, armed only with a cart and a pile of woolen ware, help to keep the knitted goods store open?

name: Signal on 1420MHz
lore: Headset foxes all over the place got a surprise after receiving a strange signal through their headsets at 1420MHz all at the same time. Each of them thought nothing of it until they spoke to other foxes across a range of call centers and broadcast booths and realized they, too, had heard it. Can your fox solve the Wow! signal and work out who or what was trying to talk to them before FASA covers it up?

name: International Fox of Mystery
lore: The name's Fox, James Fox, and the mission is far too secret to send. If you want to know more, come to the place where the lights are dim and the drinks are shaken. This message will self-destruct in 5-4-...

name: Arctic Adventure
lore: Tales have persisted of what lies beyond Foxhalla for generations, each hearing a more exaggerated version than the last. Originally meant as a warning, these tales told of monsters made of snow and ice, so when a Penguin comes to the settlement of Bilskirnir requesting help, foxes jump at the opportunity. Will your fox brave the frigid wastelands and find what lurks there?

name: The Gentlefox's Club
lore: There are a long list of traits which define a gentlefox: he must possess a healthy dose of masculinity, a taste for the finer things in life, a chivalrous attitude to the fairer sex, but mostly an accent which can only be honed in the hatter's district of Foxton. Your fox has the hat, but does he have the moves to cement his place in high society?

name: The Fast and The Curious
lore: Outside of The Hallowed Skulk, few foxes are ever invited to Hyperuranion, but recently whispers have been doing the rounds in the heavenly town speaking of a club of foxes who love to race: The Black Valets. The Valets have been asked by some of the more earthly hallowed foxes to perform in an exhibition race staged in the lands of the Skulk. Can your fox outwit and outrace all the others to take the gold in this unique competition?

name: In Search of Sunrise
lore: In the sleepy town of Kruger lives a scarcely-known organization of hipster photographers known as The Buckets. Wearing their signature bucket hats, these foxes go out in search of great scenes to post on the 'gram, starring themselves, of course. Recently, a competition has started to capture the perfect sunrise. Can your fox scour the lands in search of the dopest gradients and the sweetest setting?

name: What Can I Say Except...
lore: The beach foxes love to chill for most of the year, but the college holidays are a perfect time to earn some much-needed coin for the local residents. An unexpected opening to rent one of the pop-up beach bars provides a perfect opportunity to prove your fox can mix the perfect pina colada and serve the most delicious seafood.

name: The Missing Precious
lore: Legends have been told about a ring with strange runes which has magical properties, and your fox is sure that their eyes have laid upon such a ring, the problem is, they're not sure where. Their den isn't exactly the most organized place in Greenfields, and the last thing they can do is ask for help to find it. Can your fox find the lost jewellery and uncover its magic?

name: Spring Break
lore: The leaves are blooming, the weather is growing milder, and the pollen is making everyone's eyes itch incessantly. Spring is in the air, and that can mean only one thing: The Orange Festival is in town. Foxes from near and far compete in a series of challenges for prizes, trophies, and most importantly, bragging rights. Can your fox take the gold for shooting some hoops, or will they be watching from the sidelines?

name: Mom's Spaghetti
lore: Of all the Festival's competitions, few are as highly regarded as the cooking contest. Hosted by famous TV chef, Vulxen Ramsey, the contest is televised to the entire nation, with the winner receiving an offer to work as head chef under the famously furious personality. Armed with mom's best pasta recipe, does your fox have what it takes to win the ultimate competition?

name: A Studious Solution
lore: Whilst most foxes choose to participate in feats of physical daring during The Orange Festival, those with a more intellectual nature are invited to what's billed as the toughest trivia known to foxkind. Does your fox have the smarts to win the grand prize?

name: Tales From The Seven Seas
lore: The Festival, for most foxes, is a time for competitions and showing off their skills, but the captains' skills aren't particularly apparent on dry land. They don't allow that simple nuisance to spoil their spring break, though, and they've assumed a regular role of entertaining the fox kits with ever-more exaggerated versions of swashbuckling tales of old. Can your fox find the props they need in their den to tell the greatest seafaring story of all?

name: On The Up?
lore: Tradition? Peh. Who needs it? While those other foxes are busy playing games, the Solana tribe have something much better to do: trade the current run. Sure that devs will indeed do something this time, the 50xLONG plays are starting to come out. Do your foxes have the cunning and the skill to make bags, or will they get liquidated the fox out?

name: Time to Tango
lore: Tradition? Peh. Who needs it? While those other foxes are busy playing games, the Solana tribe have something much better to do: trade the current run. Sure that devs will indeed do something this time, the 50xLONG plays are starting to come out. Do your foxes have the cunning and the skill to make bags, or will they get liquidated the fox out?

name: A Bit of a Jam(bo)
lore: There's quite a commotion in central Foxton; a strange-looking creature, introducing himself as a Jambo (whatever that is), has appeared out of nowhere and can't seem to find out where home is. Can your fox befriend the strange creature and help him to find his way home?

name: Spring Break Opportunity
lore: The sun is shining, the waves are roaring, and there's a perfect pick-me-up spot at the seaside to sell baseball caps and shades to the beachgoing foxes. Can your fox find a great supplier, pick the right spot, and turn a stunning profit over spring break?

name: Copium Shortage
lore: It's been an exciting month with all of the market volatility, but that's left some foxes with a need for large doses of copium, and all of the local copium dens are out. Can your fox bring back enough copium to keep the population of Kitson stocked up?

name: Combing Through History
lore: L. F. Gordon hired an expert on historic hairdos to co-present a prime time documentary on Famous Fox News, but he came down with an illness and wasn't available for interview. Now, FFN has put out a call for any fox with a flash hairdo to present the piece. Can your fox inform the people of Foxton about the amazing history of barbering?

name: A Regal Affair
lore: Two foxes from the Crown Court have been looking for a castle for their wedding, but so far come up empty. They're really looking to put on a spectacular event, and they've reached out to other foxes of the Court for help. Can your fox convince them that your castle is the hot spot of 2022?

name: A Warrior's Honor
lore: War may be little more than a memory in Civitas Vulpes, but that doesn't stop the leadership from wanting every fox to remain prepared, and hosting Gladiator events every so often helps to raise awareness of the combat arts, and keep their foxes sharp for the battleground. Can your fox take on all comers and prove their honor?

name: A Search for a Secret
lore: Rumor has it that FASA has uncovered new information on the origin of the Mutant foxes, and the tribe have intelligence on where the data is being stored. A bulletin has been put out to all mutants to find someone willing to break into the facility, locate the storage, and recover the information. Can your fox help to uncover the secrets of the Mutants' history?

name: A Hairy Situation
lore: The beard and tache festival is coming up, where foxes compete for the prestigious title of Hair To The Throne. Styles each year are wackier and more intricate than the last. Can your fox come up with something innovative and interesting to win the trophy?

name: A Hymn for The Heavens
lore: The Hallowed Skulk's congregations are well known for their powerful and emotive musical numbers, and rather than stick to tradition, they like to encourage creative pursuits among their numbers and offer healthy prizes for those who contribute to their rich library of songs. Can your fox create a new melody for the congregation and write their name into the Skulk's history?

name: Shopping Spree
lore: After the successful protests against the hoodie ban in downtown Foxton, one store has decided to do a complete one-eighty to celebrate their hooded customers. Pairs of hooded foxes are being given a cart and sixty seconds to fill it with as much as possible. Whichever pair wins will get their shopping cart paid for! Can your fox win the prize?

name: Vault Cleanup
lore: Over time, Hodl Gang members often find their vaults filled not only with the one true currency, but with forks and shitcoins which need clearing out. It's coming up to the end of the tax year, and the absolute last thing your foxes want to do is file a tax return not fit for a maximalist. Can your foxes beat the deadline and file 100% in the one true currency?

name: Eyewear Entrepreneurs
lore: Foxton has a lot to offer in terms of eyewear, there's something for every style and something for every price range, and the shops are hiring cool-looking foxes to show off their range in the public square in the run-up to summer. Can your foxes pull off the coolest look in central and help to sell eyewear to the residents of Foxton?

name: Captain of the Squad
lore: With the sports season drawing to a close, Foxton United is top of the league and one game away from winning the whole competition. Unfortunately, the captain's caught a bad case of copitis and won't be able to play. As a reservist for the team, can your fox don the armband and carry the team to glory, or will Foxton United spend another summer dreaming of what could have been?

name: Dojo Restoration
lore: Foxtro has long played host to one of the most celebrated martial arts dojos in the Federation, but recently due to a string of bad weather events and fiscal mismanagement, it's fallen into a state of disrepair. Local activist groups have asked for extra paws to help with the renovations, can your fox help to restore the dojo to its former glory?

name: School's Out For Summer
lore: School is coming to an end, and your foxes have been given the undesirable task of planning the summer getaway. Armed with maps, books, and the latest travel reports, they've got to come up with an itinerary that has it all: sports for the jocks, grub for the foodies, historical sites for the nerds, and beaches for the foxes that just want to relax. Can your foxes plan the ultimate summer break, or will they be foxona non gratis when they return in the fall?

name: Fashion Frenzy
lore: When is a hat not a hat? When it's the final piece of an outfit for the Royal Derby, of course. Horseracing in the Asphodel Meadows is less about the jockeys and more about the jackets, less about the course and more about the four course dinner, and it'd be simply a travesty to not look the part. There's only one problem: the local hat shops are quickly running out of this year's fashion. Your foxes are going to be the talk of the town, the question they have to answer is whether the gossip will be envious or comedic.

name: Into Apocrypha
lore: It's not often a fox gets to meet a God, even members of the Hallowed Skulk, so to be asked to accompany one on a quest into Apocrypha is quite the event. If the legends are true, the treasures to be found beyond the Apocrypha gate are beyond comprehension. Can your fox team up with a God and battle their way to prizes unrivalled in the Federation?

name: The Call of the Seven Seas
lore: Foxhalla's residents are often called to the blue yonder, and for your fox and the crew of their longboat, this time is no different. What is different, however, is the reason for passage. Instead of a simple trade mission, a map found in the attic of your foxes' family den tells of a distant and unexplored land. Can your fox claim it for Foxhalla?

name: On The Up?
lore: Tradition? Peh. Who needs it? While those other foxes are busy playing games, the Solana tribe have something much better to do: trade the current run. Sure that devs will indeed do something this time, the 50xLONG plays are starting to come out. Do your foxes have the cunning and the skill to make bags, or will they get liquidated the fox out?

Armed only with his wits and experience, your fox is tasked with retrieving the guy who's about to become Famous for all the wrong reasons.

name: To Be A Master
lore: Monster trainer foxes have little knowledge of their history before the Federation, but there are rumors of a far-off land where monsters called Bitmon roam, ready to be captured and trained. The Guild has approved and funded an excursion beyond the reaches of Fohxto, into the fabled forest where Bitmon were sighted. Can your fox befriend a local trainer and bring back a legendary Bitmon to showcase the ancient history of the Monster Trainers?

name: It's Dangerous to Go Alone!
lore: Pixel Invaders was a popular, albeit controversial, game when the transdimensional foxes arrived in Foxton. Described by L F Gordon as 'the hottest thing since space travel', it was a hit in every arcade up and down the land. Unfortunately, the machines had a common glitch which would short the mainboard so very few remain, but one has come up on web3Bay in recent months and your fox thinks they know how to restore it. Can they get a working home arcade box and be the envy of their friends, or will it prove a fruitless and costly endeavor?

name: And My Axe!
lore: A warrior's life is tough and often short, at least it was when there were wars to fight. The Viking and Centurion foxes preserve the ancient traditions as best they know them, holding regular gladitorial matches so that foxes can show their prowess. Can your foxes put on the best show?

name: Lazy Sunday
lore: The traditional hillside houses of Foxton aren't every fox's cup of tea, but those who like them love them, and Foxton holds a regular celebration of this particular part of their heritage. Can your foxes out-decorate and out-renovate all the other foxes and take home the Baggins Prize?

name: This Life Chose Me
lore: The rap battle scene in Upper Foxton is heating up, and there's a record deal with Robbin' Hoodz Records on the line for whoever can top the competition this weekend. Entry is well-guarded, with only those who have shown their skills on the mic invited to participate. Can your fox outwit the biggest players on the scene and win the elusive deal?

name: An Uber Idea
lore: Hayes Valley doesn't need more valets, but there's a huge shortage of minicabs in the tech hub, and it's not for a lack of customers. Your foxes have an idea: an app to allow foxes to load up some Solana and use their phone to book a ride to anywhere in the area. Can they take the market by storm, with one on dispatch and the other driving, or will the idea be an uber fail?

name: The Treasure of Shipwreck Cove
lore: Rumor has it that the ancient treasures of Captain Blacktail are buried somewhere near Shipwreck Cove, but do you have the seafaring skills to find it? Tales tell of an emerald imbued ring that confers the power to control the winds, but they're probably nothing -- either way, it's expensive. This mission isn't for the landlubbers, so what say ye?

name: Dynamic Duo
lore: The only thing better than a fox on a mission is two foxes on a mission (or three foxes on a mission, but that's just being pedantic). A secret cave entrance has been discovered in the mountains near Foxhalla, naturally accompanied with slew of warning signs and rumors about ancient treasures. Can your foxes descend the cave together and chart new territory for all of foxkind?

name: Don’t Stare At It
lore: It's no secret that mutants and scarred foxes catch some stares in public, especially in the less open-minded parts of the federation. Your foxes have been invited to pen a piece for WAGMI Blog to help to change perceptions around foxes who look different. Will they convince others to open up their minds, or just close them further?

name: Return to Monke
lore: Beyond the borders of the federation is a place: an ancient civilization of wise simians who have been around for as long as anyone can remember. Their lands are a strange place, with blocky buildings and blocky trees, and famous citizens abound. Contact between these monkeys and foxes has just been established, but one thing's clear: adventure is on the agenda. The monkeys love to explore ancient ruins, searching for long-lost artifacts and knowledge, or just to test their mettle. Can your fox find a monkey partner and find their place in history?

name: Moonshot Dreams
lore: Deep in downtown Kitson lies the casino district: home to the deprived, degenerate, and the lucky. There are whispers of an underground ring for the best card players, where thousands of FOXY are won and lost in a single round of cards. Can you pull off a winning night at the illustrious table, or will you just be left huffing copium?

name: A Foxing Beachside Bonanza
lore: With summer fun in full swing, foxes young and old have flocked to the beaches of Rio de Foxerio. Sporting their most tropical pineapple shirts & tanks tops, foxes all over the beach are teaming up with one goal in mind—concocting the most delicious beverages to accompany the beautiful weather! Blending up all those zesty pineapple smoothies and pouring mojitos has caught the attention of the other beach goers and a line has formed at your make-shift cantina, can your foxes keep up with the demand and deliver good vibes (and drinks) to all?

name: Le Festival du Hats
lore: Fancy hats and mint juleps. Race on over to the Windsor hat festival, where foxes from around the globe gather to revel in fabulous toppers. Indulge in fashion shows and cocktail reception amongst socialite personalities... Attend professional milliner workshops.. Or perhaps,  take part in hat design contests with up-and-coming young hat-makers... Surely this is an event your fox wouldn't want to miss?

name: Le Festival du Hats #2
lore: Fancy hats and mint juleps. Race on over to the Windsor hat festival, where foxes from around the globe gather to revel in fabulous toppers. Indulge in fashion shows and cocktail reception amongst socialite personalities... Attend professional milliner workshops.. Or perhaps,  take part in hat design contests with up-and-coming young hat-makers... Surely this is an event your fox wouldn't want to miss?

name: Captain of the Squad #2
lore: With the sports season drawing to a close, Foxton United is top of the league and one game away from winning the whole competition. Unfortunately, the captain's caught a bad case of copitis and won't be able to play. As a reservist for the team, can your fox don the armband and carry the team to glory, or will Foxton United spend another summer dreaming of what could have been?

name: Captain of the Squad #3
lore: With the sports season drawing to a close, Foxton United is top of the league and one game away from winning the whole competition. Unfortunately, the captain's caught a bad case of copitis and won't be able to play. As a reservist for the team, can your fox don the armband and carry the team to glory, or will Foxton United spend another summer dreaming of what could have been?

name: The Captain Furfang Conundrum
lore: Captain Furfang's legacy is famous among the Captain's guild, and none of his adventures is more famous than his rivalry with Captain Jack Burrows. Now, the Guild has come upon a mysterious unsigned message, which claims to know the location of Furfang's remains, and his prized coat and hat. The problem is, they're at the bottom of the ocean. Can your foxes finally prove the existence of their Guild's legend, and return his prized possessions to the Guildhouse?

name: Mom's Spaghetti #2
lore: Of all the Festival's competitions, few are as highly regarded as the cooking contest. Hosted by famous TV chef, Vulxen Ramsey, the contest is televised to the entire nation, with the winner receiving an offer to work as head chef under the famously furious personality. Armed with mom's best pasta recipe, does your fox have what it takes to win the ultimate competition?

name: The Lunar Landing
lore: This is it, the ultimate purpose of FASA: the conquest of the harshest realities of nature to reach the Moon. Space is an unnatural atmosphere for foxes, composed entirely of threats which could prevent the uninitiated from reaching the moon. Low oxygen, potential impacts with debris, bearish sentiment and the dreaded FUD monster won't stop FASA from reaching its target though, will it?

name: Signal on 1420MHz
lore: Headset foxes all over the place got a surprise after receiving a strange signal through their headsets at 1420MHz all at the same time. Each of them thought nothing of it until they spoke to other foxes across a range of call centers and broadcast booths and realized they, too, had heard it. Can your fox solve the Wow! signal and work out who or what was trying to talk to them before FASA covers it up?

name: Lost in the Wilderness
lore: The call has just come in at the Safari hut. Another fox has gone off-track looking for the perfect selfie for their influencer blog. Unfortunately, selfies with lions and tigers don't always end well for the one taking them. Armed only with his wits and experience, your fox is tasked with retrieving the guy who's about to become Famous for all the wrong reasons.

name: Like No One Ever Was
lore: Monster trainers do their thing all year around, but once a year, Fohxto hosts the Orange League Championship: an intercontinental tournament of the brightest and bravest foxes and their partners. Only the most elite will make their way to the Orange League finals in Foxter City. Will your fox be among them?

name: It's Dangerous to Go Alone!
lore: Pixel Invaders was a popular, albeit controversial, game when the transdimensional foxes arrived in Foxton. Described by L F Gordon as 'the hottest thing since space travel', it was a hit in every arcade up and down the land. Unfortunately, the machines had a common glitch which would short the mainboard so very few remain, but one has come up on web3Bay in recent months and your fox thinks they know how to restore it. Can they get a working home arcade box and be the envy of their friends, or will it prove a fruitless and costly endeavor?

name: Be Prepared!
lore: Scarred foxes have long been subject to legends among other foxes; sometimes, these legends lionize them as great warriors, but other times, they associate them with a character from a certain movie about lions. In order to retain their more positive perception, scarred foxes often take it upon themselves to do something exceptionally brave. So when a tornado comes to town, your fox takes it upon themself to lead the others to safety! Can they find a safe route out of town?

name: International Fox of Mystery
lore: The name's Fox, James Fox, and the mission is far too secret to send. If you want to know more, come to the place where the lights are dim and the drinks are shaken. This message will self-destruct in 5-4-...

name: The Fox and the Gecko
lore: One of the early ancestral foxes had once befriended a gecko crash landing through a rift from a different universe. The unlikely friendship blossomed as the two learn more about each other, themselves and their places in their societies. Centuries later, this ancestral pact is due for a renewal through a hunting mission demanding trust, teamwork and tenacity. Will your fox & gecko emerge victorious through this trial of friendship?

name: The Lunar Landing
lore: This is it, the ultimate purpose of FASA: the conquest of the harshest realities of nature to reach the Moon. name: Spring Break
lore: The leaves are blooming, the weather is growing milder, and the pollen is making everyone's eyes itch incessantly. Spring is in the air, and that can mean only one thing: The Orange Festival is in town. Foxes from near and far compete in a series of challenges for prizes, trophies, and most importantly, bragging rights. Can your fox take the gold for shooting some hoops, or will they be watching from the sidelines?

name: The Ihsotas Otomakan
lore: Foxes who wish to ascend to the highest ranks of the Hallowed Skulk are tasked with a process, starting at the Elyssian Plains, which will push their mind, body and spirit to the absolute limits. Only those who achieve the higher state at the Hyperuranion will achieve ascension into the Skulk's inner circle. Is your fox ready for the ultimate challenge?

name: School of Fox
lore: The Games are well known among the collegiate. A series of competitions between the four great institutions of academia which confer prizes, the right to host the next Games, but most of all, bragging rights. Can your fox show the smarts, the wits, and the gusto to lead the College to victory?

name: On The Up?
lore: Tradition? Peh. Who needs it? While those other foxes are busy playing games, the Solana tribe have something much better to do: trade the current run. Sure that devs will indeed do something this time, the 50xLONG plays are starting to come out. Do your foxes have the cunning and the skill to make bags, or will they get liquidated the fox out?

name: Dummies and Dummier
lore: Tales have persisted of what lies beyond Foxhalla for generations, each hearing a more exaggerated version than the last. Originally meant as a warning, these tales told of monsters made of snow and ice, so when a Penguin comes to the settlement of Bilskirnir requesting help, foxes jump at the opportunity. Will your fox brave the frigid wastelands and find what lurks there?

name: The Treasure of Shipwreck Cove
lore: Rumor has it that the ancient treasures of Captain Blacktail are buried somewhere near Shipwreck Cove, but do you have the seafaring skills to find it? Tales tell of an emerald imbued ring that confers the power to control the winds, but they're probably nothing -- either way, it's expensive. This mission isn't for the landlubbers, so what say ye?

name: What Can I Say Except...
lore: The beach foxes love to chill for most of the year, but the college holidays are a perfect time to earn some much-needed coin for the local residents. An unexpected opening to rent one of the pop-up beach bars provides a perfect opportunity to prove your fox can mix the perfect pina colada and serve the most delicious seafood.

name: Hats off, hats on!
lore: Blotches of reds, yellows and oranges swirled around them as the wind picked up the autumn leaves… While other foxes had their Monster trainer baseball caps, beanies and newspaper boy caps, some foxes had never owned a single headwear in their life! But with the changing weather, will your fox be able to secure a fancy (and functional!) headpiece and keep warm this fall?

name: Captain of the Squad
lore: With the sports season drawing to a close, Foxton United is top of the league and one game away from winning the whole competition. Unfortunately, the captain's caught a bad case of copitis and won't be able to play. As a reservist for the team, can your fox don the armband and carry the team to glory, or will Foxton United spend another summer dreaming of what could have been?

name: Prepare for Glory
lore: In Civitas Vulpes, much ado is made about history -- historical leaders, historical romances, but most of all, historical battles. Unfortunately, much of this is based on rumor and legend, as there are few verifiable recordings of that far back in time. One rumor has it that the land upon which Trastevere now sits played host to the Battle of the Bushels, and that the evidence may lay below the city itself in a secret network of tunnels that were used in wartime to deliver messages. Will your fox be able to locate the tunnels, and recover ancient artefacts which would restore Trastevere to glory?

name: The First Foxiversary
lore:
The Great Hall in Foxton is bustling with excitement over the weekend-long celebration of the Federation turning 1! Balloons, streamers and of course, orange circle confetti decorate every inch of the multi-story venue, where foxes far and wide have come together to celebrate the journey we've collectively gone through together. Through a Portals card, any and all foxes are invited to join trivia games, great food and banger k-pop songs, what's your fox  waiting for? Get over here and join the party! 
Here's to another great year ahead. Let's Foxing Go, foxes.

name: The Critter Return
lore: Swarms of creatures--Critters, as they call themselves-- have been found around Foxton the past few weeks. These Occultist Society members said they came through a 'spiral' pattern in a songless forest sky, to the streets of the Federation. It is now up to your Fox to bring their Critter buddy back to this mysterious Research Facility in a nameless suburban industrial town...

name: The Fast and The Curious
lore: Outside of The Hallowed Skulk, few foxes are ever invited to Hyperuranion, but recently whispers have been doing the rounds in the heavenly town speaking of a club of foxes who love to race: The Black Valets. The Valets have been asked by some of the more earthly hallowed foxes to perform in an exhibition race staged in the lands of the Skulk. Can your fox outwit and outrace all the others to take the gold in this unique competition?

name: Spring Break
lore: The leaves are blooming, the weather is growing milder, and the pollen is making everyone's eyes itch incessantly. Spring is in the air, and that can mean only one thing: The Orange Festival is in town. Foxes from near and far compete in a series of challenges for prizes, trophies, and most importantly, bragging rights. Can your fox take the gold for shooting some hoops, or will they be watching from the sidelines?

name: A Hymn for The Heavens
lore: The Hallowed Skulk's congregations are well known for their powerful and emotive musical numbers, and rather than stick to tradition, they like to encourage creative pursuits among their numbers and offer healthy prizes for those who contribute to their rich library of songs. Can your fox create a new melody for the congregation and write their name into the Skulk's history?

name: Nap Attack
lore: A very unconventional mission has been listed. Whether you’re trying to recover from 2 all-nighters playing some foxtendo switch or just needing to clear the brain fog, sleepy foxes are all mandated to take a nap! Send your sleepy fox to recharge their physical and social battery to tackle on other adventures after.

lore: Foxton has a lot to offer in terms of eyewear, there's something for every style and something for every price range, and the shops are hiring cool-looking foxes to show off their range in the public square in the run-up to summer. Can your foxes pull off the coolest look in central and help to sell eyewear to the residents of Foxton?

name: A Regal Affair
lore: Two foxes from the Crown Court have been looking for a castle for their wedding, but so far come up empty. They're really looking to put on a spectacular event, and they've reached out to other foxes of the Court for help. Can your fox convince them that your castle is the hot spot of 2022?

name: Tales From The Seven Seas
lore: The Festival, for most foxes, is a time for competitions and showing off their skills, but the captains' skills aren't particularly apparent on dry land. They don't allow that simple nuisance to spoil their spring break, though, and they've assumed a regular role of entertaining the fox kits with ever-more exaggerated versions of swashbuckling tales of old. Can your fox find the props they need in their den to tell the greatest seafaring story of all?

name: The Missing Precious
lore: Legends have been told about a ring with strange runes which has magical properties, and your fox is sure that their eyes have laid upon such a ring, the problem is, they're not sure where. Their den isn't exactly the most organized place in Greenfields, and the last thing they can do is ask for help to find it. Can your fox find the lost jewellery and uncover its magic?

Can your fox navigate the treacherous waters and restore the town's most important resource?

lore: L. F. Gordon hired an expert on historic hairdos to co-present a prime time documentary on Famous Fox News, but he came down with an illness and wasn't available for interview. Now, FFN has put out a call for any fox with a flash hairdo to present the piece. Can your fox inform the people of Foxton about the amazing history of barbering?

name: Copium Shortage
lore: It's been an exciting month with all of the market volatility, but that's left some foxes with a need for large doses of copium, and all of the local copium dens are out. Can your fox bring back enough copium to keep the population of Kitson stocked up?

lore: Mutant dens are not like other dens, and other foxes have noticed it for a long time. It's fuelled all kinds of rumors: are the mutants psychic? Do they come from a nuclear catastrophe? The reality, of course, is quite a bit harder to believe. The tribe themselves have long been known to keep their origins a secret, especially from those probing minds at FASA, and with new legislation pending which would allow FASA to investigate, there's not much time to hide the evidence. Can your fox lead the mutant tribe to protect the secrets of their origins?

It's up to your fanged friend to undergo a test of palate and procurement to recreate the sauce from taste alone.

name: The Sword From The Stone
lore: Does a crown alone make a King? Or is there more to it? Legends say that when the genesis block was formed, Hexcalibur -- or 0xcalibur as it's known in the Ether Lands -- was formed with it, inside of a rock formation. In the mythos, whoever can pull the sword from its resting place shall be recognized as the King of foxkind, though it's just as likely he'll just have a very cool-looking sword. Still, worth a try, right?

name: A Hairy Situation
lore: The beard and tache festival is coming up, where foxes compete for the prestigious title of Hair To The Throne. Styles each year are wackier and more intricate than the last. Can your fox come up with something innovative and interesting to win the trophy?
